<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.4.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://benshui.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://benshui.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2026-07-24T07:30:25+00:00</updated><id>https://benshui.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">blank</title><subtitle>Jiahui&apos;s Personal Website | PhD student at UCSD </subtitle><entry><title type="html">Research “Taste”</title><link href="https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/research-taste/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Research “Taste”"/><published>2026-07-14T19:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-07-14T19:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/research-taste</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/research-taste/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="misc"/><category term="misc"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[What is "research taste"?]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Pre-FOMC Announcement Drift</title><link href="https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/pre-fomc-drift/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pre-FOMC Announcement Drift"/><published>2026-05-30T19:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2026-05-30T19:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/pre-fomc-drift</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://benshui.github.io/blog/2026/pre-fomc-drift/"><![CDATA[<p>Pre-FOMC drift replicates and is roughly halved post-2011. On SPY minute bars 2000–2026 the average 09:30 (day t−1) → 14:15 (day t) drift is +36 bps (n=209 scheduled meetings); splitting at 2012-01-01 gives +48 bps pre vs +25 bps post. The break aligns with Lucca &amp; Moench’s NY Fed staff report (2011).</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="asset-pricing"/><category term="asset-pricing"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[The disappearing pre-FOMC announcement drift]]></summary></entry></feed>